b'[<p><i><b>UFC 42: Sudden Impact</b></i> was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> on April 25, 2003, at <a href="/wiki/American_Airlines_Arena" title="American Airlines Arena">American Airlines Arena</a> in <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Miami,_Florida" title="Miami, Florida">Miami, Florida</a>.  The event was broadcast live on <a href="/wiki/Pay-per-view" title="Pay-per-view">pay-per-view</a> in the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a>, and later released on <a href="/wiki/DVD" title="DVD">DVD</a>.\n</p>, <p>UFC 42 was the first <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">UFC</a> event to take place in <a href="/wiki/Florida" title="Florida">Florida</a>.  Headlining the event was a <a href="/wiki/Welterweight_(MMA)" title="Welterweight (MMA)">Welterweight</a> Title bout between <a href="/wiki/Matt_Hughes_(fighter)" title="Matt Hughes (fighter)">Matt Hughes</a> and <a href="/wiki/Sean_Sherk" title="Sean Sherk">Sean Sherk</a>. UFC 42 also marked the first <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">UFC</a> appearance of future <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Middleweight_Championship" title="UFC Middleweight Championship">Middleweight Champion</a> <a href="/wiki/Rich_Franklin" title="Rich Franklin">Rich Franklin</a>.\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Joe_Rogan" title="Joe Rogan">Joe Rogan</a> provided the lead commentary for this event and was joined by colour commentator <a href="/wiki/Phil_Baroni" title="Phil Baroni">Phil Baroni</a> with further analysis by <a href="/wiki/Eddie_Bravo" title="Eddie Bravo">Eddie Bravo</a>.\n</p>]'